attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, version 1 (ARM), statically linked, no section header

threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is an ARM-based IoT botnet agent, likely a variant of the Gafgyt (BASHLITE) or Mirai families. It is designed to establish a Command and Control (C2) connection to the hardcoded IP 151.243.109.76. The sample exhibits classic malicious behaviors, including multiple DDoS attack vectors (e.g., SSDP M-SEARCH floods, TCP/UDP floods seen in functions like sub_f618 and sub_e9d4), and a routine to scan the /proc filesystem to identify and kill rival malware processes (sub_fd18). It employs string obfuscation (sub_11614) to hinder analysis and includes signature strings such as 'Self Rep Fucking NeTiS', which are common in automated exploitation scripts targeting IoT vulnerabilities.
